  <Docs>
    <summary>Specifies the arguments used to clone a typeface with custom variation positions and palette settings.</summary>
    <remarks><format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[
## Remarks

`SKFontArguments` is a `ref struct` that bundles arguments used to clone a
typeface with specific variation positions, a palette index, and palette color
overrides. Pass it to <xref:SkiaSharp.SKTypeface.Clone(SkiaSharp.SKFontArguments)>
to obtain a new typeface configured with the specified settings.

Because `SKFontArguments` is a `ref struct`, it cannot be stored on the heap or
used across `async` boundaries. The spans it holds must remain valid for the
lifetime of the struct.

## Examples

```csharp
// Clone a variable font at a specific weight axis position
var coordinate = new SKFontVariationPositionCoordinate
{
    Axis = SKFourByteTag.Parse("wght"),
    Value = 700f,
};

var args = new SKFontArguments
{
    VariationDesignPosition = new[] { coordinate },
    PaletteIndex = 0,
};

using var boldTypeface = typeface.Clone(args);
```
]]></format></remarks>
  </Docs>
